# LearnGraph — Core Standards

## Stack (exact versions matter)
- **Runtime**: Next.js 16 (App Router), TypeScript 5 strict mode
- **Styling**: Tailwind v4 — CSS-native `@theme` in `globals.css`. NEVER use `tailwind.config.ts`
- **UI**: shadcn/ui (New York style) + Radix primitives
- **API**: tRPC v11 — ALL procedures require Zod input validation
- **DB**: Drizzle ORM + Supabase Postgres + pgvector (1536 dims)
- **Auth**: Supabase Auth
- **State**: TanStack Query (server) + React state/Context (client)
- **AI**: Vercel AI SDK — Claude Sonnet 4.5 (primary), GPT-4.1-mini (fallback), text-embedding-3-small
- **Package manager**: pnpm + Turborepo monorepo

## Monorepo Layout
```
apps/web/src/         → Next.js app, alias @/
packages/db/          → @repo/db  — Drizzle schema + client
packages/ai/          → @repo/ai  — LLM orchestration + ingestion pipeline
packages/fsrs/        → @repo/fsrs — FSRS-5 scheduler (zero external deps)
packages/shared/      → @repo/shared — shared types, constants, utils
```

## Naming & File Conventions
- `type` over `interface` for data shapes
- Drizzle inferred types: `typeof table.$inferSelect`
- tRPC routers: one file per domain in `apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/`
- Feature components: `apps/web/src/components/{feature}/*.tsx`
- DB schema: `packages/db/src/schema/*.ts` — one file per domain
- All DB tables MUST have `created_at timestamptz`
- RLS policies: raw `.sql` migration files ONLY — never in Drizzle schema

## NEVER
- Use default exports for components — always named exports
- Use `tailwind.config.ts` — Tailwind v4 is CSS-native
- Use raw text LLM completions — always `generateObject` with a Zod schema
- Add write-side-effect tools to the AI mentor without explicit review
- Import `toast` from anywhere except `@/components/ui/sonner`
- Install new packages without checking the docs first (`context7` MCP)

## ALWAYS
- Validate tRPC inputs with Zod from day 1
- Every async UI operation needs loading + error + empty states
- Check resource ownership before any LLM call or data return
- Use `hsl(var(--token))` pattern for color values
